parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Takata Airbag Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable repairs for the Takata airbag recall can leave the vehicle occupants at risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: as the complaints are related to the unavailability of parts or delays in the repair process
rather than a specific symptom or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail to function properly, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail to function properly, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuators can cause inconvenience and compromise vehicle security, making it difficult for occupants to enter or exit the vehicle.
symptoms: Multiple doors (typically three or more) do not lock or unlock electronically
doors do not respond to keyless entry or remote commands
doors do not lock or unlock when using the door lock switch.
